1257
01:19:45,440 --> 01:19:47,280
Seems like a very
complicated formula,

1258
01:19:47,280 --> 01:19:49,360
but it's not really
a complicated one.

1259
01:19:49,360 --> 01:19:53,600
I'm going to just explain in
plain terms what this means.

1260
01:19:53,600 --> 01:19:55,120
So J of GRPO--

1261
01:19:55,120 --> 01:19:56,880
J means objective function.

1262
01:19:56,880 --> 01:20:01,680
So the objective
function of GRPO

1263
01:20:01,680 --> 01:20:06,640
is to maximize this
quantity, which

1264
01:20:06,640 --> 01:20:10,800
is a function of how
much your model changes

1265
01:20:10,800 --> 01:20:12,160
with respect to the old one.

1266
01:20:12,160 --> 01:20:15,920
So it's these ratios that
you see in the slide.

1267
01:20:15,920 --> 01:20:17,760
And you have this
clipping mechanism

1268
01:20:17,760 --> 01:20:23,440
that prevents your updates
from being too wide.

1269
01:20:23,440 --> 01:20:26,480
And then you have
the KL divergence

1270
01:20:26,480 --> 01:20:31,120
on the right, which prevents
your model from being too far

1271
01:20:31,120 --> 01:20:32,960
from the base model.

1272
01:20:32,960 --> 01:20:35,440
The reference model.

1273
01:20:35,440 --> 01:20:38,560
And then you have
these summations here

1274
01:20:38,560 --> 01:20:39,760
and the summations here.

1275
01:20:39,760 --> 01:20:45,040
They correspond to you
going through that process

1276
01:20:45,040 --> 01:20:48,400
for all completions
in your group.

1277
01:20:48,400 --> 01:20:51,120
Because remember if you
have a prompt you sample

1278
01:20:51,120 --> 01:20:55,040
several times have
several completions,

1279
01:20:55,040 --> 01:21:00,720
and then you do that for
every token of your output.

1280
01:21:00,720 --> 01:21:05,360
So here, the first summation is
over the indices of your group.

1281
01:21:05,360 --> 01:21:08,880
The second summation
is over the indices

1282
01:21:08,880 --> 01:21:14,160
that are with respect to the
token number in your sequence.

1283
01:21:14,160 --> 01:21:18,640
And so here, I guess let's
just think for a second,

1284
01:21:18,640 --> 01:21:20,400
if we were to swap--

1285
01:21:20,400 --> 01:21:23,440
I'm not sure if you
