1298
01:22:11,360 --> 01:22:14,400
So in other words,
the contribution

1299
01:22:14,400 --> 01:22:19,440
of a token with respect
to the objective function

1300
01:22:19,440 --> 01:22:23,440
depends on the
output that it is in.

1301
01:22:24,400 --> 01:22:28,400
So if the token is
in a short sentence,

1302
01:22:28,400 --> 01:22:30,800
it's going to have a
higher weight bigger weight

1303
01:22:30,800 --> 01:22:36,000
than in a longer sentence.

1304
01:22:36,000 --> 01:22:40,560
Until now, is everyone
agreeing with me?

1305
01:22:40,560 --> 01:22:43,040
Yeah?

1306
01:22:43,920 --> 01:22:46,880
So with that being
said, I'm just

1307
01:22:46,880 --> 01:22:49,360
going to rephrase
what I just said,

1308
01:22:50,160 --> 01:22:53,840
if you are in a short
sentence, your weight

1309
01:22:53,840 --> 01:23:00,080
will be bigger than if you're
in the bigger sentence.

1310
01:23:01,600 --> 01:23:08,560
Now let's try to think about
this in terms of the advantage.

1311
01:23:08,560 --> 01:23:14,320
If you are in the case of a
token being in an output that

1312
01:23:14,320 --> 01:23:18,720
is of advantage,
that is positive,

1313
01:23:18,720 --> 01:23:23,760
that means that we
would want to upweight

1314
01:23:23,760 --> 01:23:26,880
the probability of this
token happening again,

1315
01:23:26,880 --> 01:23:32,480
much more for short sentences
as opposed to longer ones.

1316
01:23:32,480 --> 01:23:39,600
And at the same time, you want,
when the advantage is negative--

1317
01:23:39,600 --> 01:23:40,640
so it's not you want.

1318
01:23:40,640 --> 01:23:43,200
It's just that
this formulation--

1319
01:23:43,200 --> 01:23:47,840
makes tokens that
are in short outputs

1320
01:23:47,840 --> 01:23:51,760
be down weighted even
more compared to when

1321
01:23:51,760 --> 01:23:55,040
they're in a long output.

1322
01:23:55,040 --> 01:23:58,960
And so this is the problem.

1323
01:23:58,960 --> 01:24:02,080
This is a bad
incentive because what

1324
01:24:02,080 --> 01:24:09,680
